verses.verse: Praise <WH1984> you the LORD. <WH3050> Praise <WH1984> the LORD, <WH3068> O my soul. <WH5315>
While I live <WH2416> will I praise <WH1984> the LORD: <WH3068> I will sing <WH2167> praises to my God <WH430> while <WH5750> I have any being. <WH5750>
Put not your trust <WH982> in princes, <WH5081> nor in the son <WH1121> of man, <WH120> in whom there is no <WH369> help. <WH8668>
His breath <WH7307> goes <WH3318> forth, <WH3318> he returns <WH7725> to his earth; <WH127> in that very day <WH3117> his thoughts <WH6250> perish. <WH6>

Which executes <WH6213> judgment <WH4941> for the oppressed: <WH6231> which gives <WH5414> food <WH3899> to the hungry. <WH7456> The LORD <WH3068> looses <WH5425> the prisoners: <WH631>

The LORD <WH3068> preserves <WH8104> the strangers; <WH1616> he relieves <WH5749> the fatherless <WH3490> and widow: <WH490> but the way <WH1870> of the wicked <WH7563> he turns <WH5791> upside down.
The LORD <WH3068> shall reign <WH4427> for ever, <WH5769> even your God, <WH430> O Zion, <WH6726> to all generations. <WH1755> Praise <WH1984> you the LORD. <WH3050>
